# Quiet Daily Life UI [QDL-*]

Canon: `docs/v2/QUIET_DAILY_LIFE_DOCTRINE.md`

## Governing principle

The system may be complex underneath; volunteer surfaces must feel **calm, personal, and obvious**.

## Before changing volunteer-facing UI

1. **One primary action** per viewport — no competing CTAs.
2. **Plain language** — never show: scope resolver, mutation coverage, shadow parity, CPOS, build phase, Postgres/authority jargon.
3. **Progressive disclosure** — title + one line + status + next action; details behind "View details".
4. **Audience band** — match [Audience Sectioning](docs/v2/AUDIENCE_SECTIONING_DOCTRINE.md); no upward leakage of Operator/Architect chrome.
5. **No empty modules** — hide unused nav; use helpful empty states.
6. **Mobile first** for Today · Community · Calendar · People · Me.

## Copy examples

| Avoid | Use |
|-------|-----|
| Operational readiness dimension | Your next meeting |
| Postgres authority shadow mode | Some changes may take longer to appear |
| User dashboard | My home / organizing home |

## Training

Use one label: **Learn how** — drawer with what / three steps / why / full lesson.

## Manager person view

When leaders click a user, show: work, interests, **availability calendar**, locations, committee work — not engineering or certification internals.
